; X-axis resonance / stability stimulus (not the ferror campaign move).
; Short stroke + high feed so accel/reversals excite mechanical modes.
; Use with Servo Tuning FERR plot + listen/feel for buzz/ring after each reverse.
; Prerequisites: homed (or safe work offset), clear travel around X0, soft gains OK.
;
; If it screams immediately: Abort, lower C01.01 / C01.03, then retry.
G21              ; mm
G90              ; absolute
G94              ; feed per minute
G61              ; exact path — sharper reversals than G64 blend
G0 X0            ; start at work zero

#1 = 8           ; reversal cycles
#2 = 3.0         ; stroke mm (keep small; raise only if still too gentle)
#3 = 30000       ; mm/min — near machine capability so accel dominates

o100 while [#1 gt 0]
  G1 X[#2] F[#3]
  G4 P0.25       ; brief settle — listen/watch for ring
  G1 X0 F[#3]
  G4 P0.25
  #1 = [#1 - 1]
o100 endwhile

; Optional second pass: slightly longer stroke, same aggressiveness
#1 = 4
#2 = 6.0
o110 while [#1 gt 0]
  G1 X[#2] F[#3]
  G4 P0.25
  G1 X0 F[#3]
  G4 P0.25
  #1 = [#1 - 1]
o110 endwhile

G64 P0.001       ; restore typical path mode from machine startup
G0 X0
M2
